The Chronicle Temba Dube, Deputy News Editor
Police in Bulawayo have arrested a second suspect into the brutal suspected ritual murder of a 25-year-old woman. The unnamed suspect is said to have been involved in disposing of Thabelo Mazolo’s body. He was arrested over the weekend. Tawana Ngwenya was arrested last week in Harare after allegedly killing Mazolo and putting her remains in a drum filled with acid. <img class="wp-image-500431 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/06/Tawana-Ngwenya-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/06/Tawana-Ngwenya.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/06/Tawana-Ngwenya-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Tawana Ngwenya The suspects are expected to appear in court today. Ngwenya allegedly killed Mazolo in a blood ritual to get riches…